BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:73894f57172e9621@kidcal
DTSTAMP:20260723T122613Z
DTSTART:20260723T193000Z
DTEND:20260723T203000Z
SUMMARY:Kids STEAM: Leaf Clay Dish
LOCATION:Kay Fox Room
URL:https://keenenh.libcal.com/event/16810072
CATEGORIES:kids\,Keene Public Library
DESCRIPTION:Play around with petrification by creating an air-dry clay lea
 f molded dish. You can bring any leaf you want\, but we will have plenty o
 f leaves available!\n\nFor ages 5 - 12 and their caregivers. \n\nRegistrat
 ion is required.\n\nPlease not that participants later than 15 minutes may
  have their spots given to those on the waitlist.\nSource: Keene Public Li
 brary
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:faa001d4ed2a7ff2@kidcal
DTSTAMP:20260723T122613Z
DTSTART:20260725T150000Z
DTEND:20260725T170000Z
SUMMARY:Lindsay Acela & her Puppet Pals
LOCATION:Heberton Hall
URL:https://keenenh.libcal.com/event/16635300
CATEGORIES:kids\,Keene Public Library
DESCRIPTION:Lindsay is back with her larger-than-life Puppet Pals in this 
 funny\, fast-paced\, and highly interactive variety show that will delight
  our youngest friends and the young at heart! You never know who you might
  meet. Perhaps a goofy moose\, a heroic tiger\, or a lovable bear. Oh my! 
 Maybe a dancing robot or flamingo\, a spunky chicken\, a stubborn goat\, a
  shy dragon\, or a singing dinosaur! Come find out who's making an appeara
 nce this time!\n\nLindsay has been performing full-time since 2011\, prese
 nting to several thousand children each year. Through animated storytellin
 g and thoughtful messaging\, she hopes to model social-emotional learning 
 and creative play. She believes shared joy and laughter strengthens commun
 ities of all kinds!\n\nThis program is free and is a great fit for ages 3-
 8 and families. Registration is Appreciated.\n\nFor more information conta
 ct Amy Kraemer akraemer@keenenh.gov\n\nHope to see you there!\nSource: Kee
 ne Public Library
END:VEVENT
