DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260724T180000
SUMMARY:Level Up Your Games: Games Group for School Aged Kids
LOCATION:Whiting Library\, 117 Main Street\, Chester\, VT\, 05143\, United
  States
URL:https://vermontjournal.com/event/level-up-your-games-games-group-for-s
 chool-aged-kids/2026-07-24/
CATEGORIES:kids\,Vermont Journal & Shopper
DESCRIPTION:CHESTER\, Vt. – Whiting Library provides a wide variety of g
 ames to choose from\, including classic board\, new tabletop\, fan-favorit
 e card games\, and more. \nGames are an essential component of the library
 . Information presented in new formats that encourage critical thinking an
 d problem-solving\, and games that encourage social interaction among peer
 s are just a few of the reasons to consider joining the Whiting Library Ga
 me Group.\nSource: Vermont Journal & Shopper
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:bbb7f99182d7175c@kidcal
DTSTAMP:20260723T122613Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260728T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260728T113000
SUMMARY:Playgroup for Wee Littles (0-5) and Caregivers
LOCATION:Whiting Library\, 117 Main Street\, Chester\, VT\, 05143\, United
  States
URL:https://vermontjournal.com/event/playgroup-for-wee-littles-0-5-caregiv
 ers/2026-07-28/
CATEGORIES:kids\,Vermont Journal & Shopper
DESCRIPTION:CHESTER\, Vt. – Whiting Library is home to a weekly playgrou
 p for the Wee Littles (0-5 years old) and their caregivers on Tuesdays\, f
 rom 10-11:30 a.m. This is a free\, fun\, and relaxed gathering where littl
 e kids play while their grown-ups supervise and socialize. \nYou don’t n
 eed to pre-register\; you can just drop into the library Community Room. S
 tay as long or as little as you like. Our playtime is geared towards careg
 ivers who want to find friendships and build connections with their childr
 en and the greater wee little people (0-5 years old) community. \nFun and 
 games\, plus art and craft projects in the community room downstairs – a
 vailable to enjoy when the Community Room is not booked for other events. 
 \nEveryone learns best through play. Contact our youth librarian for more 
 information via youthlibrarian@whitinglibrary.org\, or call 802-875-2277.\
 nSource: Vermont Journal & Shopper
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:3c455842feaa9617@kidcal
DTSTAMP:20260723T122613Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260729T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260729T110000
SUMMARY:Story Hour at Whiting Library!
LOCATION:Whiting Library\, 117 Main Street\, Chester\, VT\, 05143\, United
  States
URL:https://vermontjournal.com/event/story-hour-at-whiting-library/2026-07
 -29/
CATEGORIES:kids\,Vermont Journal & Shopper
DESCRIPTION:CHESTER\, Vt. – Story Hour is geared for preschoolers\, but 
 all children of all ages are encouraged to join in the fun. Enjoy stories\
 , music\, crafts\, and new book previews from Whiting Library. The storyti
 me will be adapted each week to fit the kids’ abilities in the room. Sto
 ry Hour is approximately 30-60 minutes long\, depending on the kids’ att
 ention span and interest each week.\nSource: Vermont Journal & Shopper
END:VEVENT
