BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:fa94d2fc36b532b6@kidcal
DTSTAMP:20260723T122613Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260723T103000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260723T140000
SUMMARY:Adventure Together
URL:https://sapcc-vt.org/event/adventure-together/2026-07-23/
CATEGORIES:kids\,Springfield Area Parent Child Center
DESCRIPTION:A Fun Summer Program For Families to Explore New Places Togeth
 er! \nAdventures await every Thursday starting at 10:30am from July 9-Augu
 st 13\, 2026. This is a FREE program for families with young children. \nS
 APCC removes barriers so families can safely explore new experiences\, mak
 e meaningful connections\, and build the village that supports them along 
 the way. \n————————————————– \nSchedule 
 for July\nJuly 9th – Trip to The Friendly Farm in Dublin NH. \nJuly 16th
  – Trip to Wonderfeet Kids Museum in Rutland VT. \nJuly 23rd – Trip to
  the Grafton Nature Museum \nJuly 30th – Walk at the Perkinsville Power 
 Dam in Perkinsville VT. \nSchedule for August\nAugust 6th -Walk at Distant
  Hill in Walpole NH. \nAugust 13th – Trip to Plymouth State Park in Ludl
 ow VT. \n—————————————————— \nThis yea
 r we will take 4 field trips and visit 2 nature walk locations. SAPCC prov
 ides admission costs\, $20 gas cards for families in need each travel week
 \, and lunch for everyone! Please note the weeks that the group is walking
 \, lunch and gas cards are not provided. \nRegistration will be open until
  a week before each adventure to allow us to send a head count to the visi
 ting location. Please note that you will need to research the locations pr
 ior to registration to ensure they meet the accessibility needs of your fa
 mily. \nRegistration is required and space is limited so sign up now to ge
 t on the contact list for each week’s opportunity! \nQuestions? kayla.ba
 pp@sapcc-vt.org or 802-886-5242\nSource: Springfield Area Parent Child Cen
 ter
END:VEVENT
